{"article_id":"AoJS8IxC5Xf9fX3J","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention is considering adding the names of health care workers","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"being monitored for the Ebola virus","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"to the government 's no-fly list ,","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"federal officials tell Fox News .","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"The move is being considered as a response to Wednesday 's disclosure","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"that Dallas nurse Amber Joy Vinson was cleared to fly on a commercial airliner earlier this week","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"despite having been exposed to the Ebola virus","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"while treating Thomas Edward Duncan at Texas Health Presbyterian Hospital .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"Texas health officials announced early Wednesday","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"that Vinson , 29 , had tested positive for the virus ,","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"making her the second hospital worker","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"to become infected .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"Vinson 's fellow nurse , 26-year-old Nina Pham , tested positive last weekend .","depth":5},{"id":13,"text":"More than 70 workers","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"involved in Duncan 's treatment","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"are being monitored by the CDC .","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"Duncan died Oct. 8 of the virus after nearly two weeks in the hospital .","depth":5},{"id":17,"text":"On Monday , a CDC official cleared Vinson to fly from Cleveland to Dallas on board Frontier Airlines Flight 1143","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"despite the fact","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"that she had called","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"and reported having a slight fever , one of the common symptoms of the Ebola virus .","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"Vinson 's reported temperature","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"-- 99.5 degrees --","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"was below the threshold of 100.4 degrees","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"set by the agency","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"and she had no symptoms ,","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"according to CDC spokesman David Daigle .","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"Federal sources , though , are now saying","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"she `` lied '' about how she was feeling .","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"Though she told the CDC","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"she had a low-grade fever ,","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"according to sources","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"her family said","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"she was feeling tired and not feeling well .","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"But sources said","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"this information was not conveyed to CDC officials","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"when she called","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"to ask about flying .","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"On Wednesday ,","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"after Vinson was diagnosed with Ebola ,","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"CDC Director Dr. Thomas Frieden acknowledged","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"that the nurse should not have been allowed to board the plane .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"Vinson had been in Ohio visiting family","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"and had not experienced initial symptoms during her outward journey .","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"From now on ,","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"Frieden said ,","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"no one else","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"involved in Duncan 's care","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"would be allowed to travel `` other than in a controlled environment . ''","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"He cited guidelines","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"that permit charter flights or travel by car but no public transportation .","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"Federal health officials are now attempting to track down Vinson 's fellow passengers on the flight ,","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"the CDC said Wednesday .","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"Frontier has taken the aircraft out of service .","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"The plane was flown Wednesday without passengers from Cleveland to Denver ,","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"where the airline said","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"it will undergo a fourth cleaning ,","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"including replacement of seat covers , carpeting and air filters .","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"One Central Texas school district temporarily closed three of its campuses","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"because two of its students traveled on the same flight as Vinson .","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"Early Thursday , Frontier released a statement","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"that the crew of Flight 1143 had been placed on paid leave for 21 days ,","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"despite CDC guidance","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"that they were all safe to fly .","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"On its website , the CDC says","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"all people","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"possibly exposed to Ebola","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"should restrict their travels","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"-- including by avoiding commercial flights --","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"for 21 days .","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"Also Thursday , Texas Health Presbyterian Hospital said","depth":6},{"id":72,"text":"it was offering rooms to any workers","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"being monitored for the virus","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"who wished to avoid the possibility","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"of passing the virus to family or friends .","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"Meanwhile , federal health officials ,","depth":6},{"id":77,"text":"including Frieden ,","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"were scheduled to testify before the oversight subcommittee of the House Energy and Commerce Committee Thursday .","depth":5},{"id":79,"text":"In prepared testimony , Anthony Fauci , director of the National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases at the National Institutes of Health , said","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"Duncan 's death and the infections of the two Dallas nurses and a nurse in Spain `` intensify our concerns about this global health threat . ''","depth":6},{"id":81,"text":"He said","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"two Ebola vaccine candidates were undergoing a first phase of human clinical testing this fall .","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"But he cautioned","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"that scientists were still in the early stages","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"of understanding how Ebola infection can be treated and prevented .","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"Medical records","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"provided to The Associated Press by Duncan 's family","depth":6},{"id":88,"text":"showed","depth":5},{"id":89,"text":"Vinson inserted catheters ,","depth":5},{"id":90,"text":"drew blood","depth":6},{"id":91,"text":"and dealt with Duncan 's body fluids .","depth":6},{"id":92,"text":"Late Wednesday , she arrived in Atlanta","depth":4},{"id":93,"text":"to be treated at Emory University Hospital ,","depth":5},{"id":94,"text":"which has already treated three Americans","depth":6},{"id":95,"text":"diagnosed with the virus .","depth":6},{"id":96,"text":"Also Wednesday , President Obama sought to ease fears in the U.S. ,","depth":6},{"id":97,"text":"urging a stepped-up response","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"even as he stressed","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"that the danger in the United States remained a long shot .","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"`` We want a rapid response team , a SWAT team essentially , from the CDC to be on the ground as quickly as possible , hopefully within 24 hours ,","depth":7},{"id":101,"text":"so that they are taking the local hospital step by step though what needs to be done , ''","depth":7},{"id":102,"text":"he said .","depth":6},{"id":103,"text":"But Obama also noted","depth":5},{"id":104,"text":"that the Ebola is not an airborne virus like the flu ,","depth":6},{"id":105,"text":"and thus is more difficult to transmit .","depth":6},{"id":106,"text":"The president made a point of noting","depth":5},{"id":107,"text":"that","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"when he visited with health care workers","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"who had tended to Ebola patients at Emory University Hospital in Atlanta ,","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"where Vinson was taken for further treatment","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"late Wednesday ,","depth":8},{"id":112,"text":"he hugged and kissed them","depth":7},{"id":113,"text":"without fear of infection .","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"`` They followed the protocols ,","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"they knew what they were doing , ''","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"he said .","depth":6},{"id":117,"text":"`` I felt perfectly safe","depth":6},{"id":118,"text":"doing so . ''","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":237,"left":204,"right":236,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":204,"left":135,"right":203,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":135,"left":126,"right":134,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":126,"left":122,"right":125,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"left":121,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":121,"left":120,"right":2,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":120,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":4,"right":124,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":124,"left":5,"right":123,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":134,"left":130,"right":133,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":130,"left":129,"right":12,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":127,"right":128,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":128,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":133,"left":132,"right":16,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":132,"left":131,"right"